if __name__ == '__main__':
    x = int(input())
    x = str(x)
    x = x[::-1]
    for i in range(len(x)):
        if x[i] == '0':
            x = x[:i] + '9' + x[i+1:]
        else:
            x = x[:i] + str(9-int(x[i])) + x[i+1:]
    if x[0] == '0':
        x = x[1:]
    print(x)

def inverting_digits(x):
    x = str(x)
    x = x[::-1]
    x = int(x)
    return x
